-- Europe Mulls Lower Interest Rates on Greek Loans, Welt Reports
-- B y   J a n a   R a n d o w
-- 2012-02-07T06:36:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/europe-mulls-lower-interest-rates-on-greek-loans-welt-reports.html
Euro-area governments are considering
a reduction of interest rates on bilateral loans to  Greece ,
supplementing the writedowns banks have agreed to take on the
country’s debt, German newspaper  Die Welt  reported, citing
unidentified people with knowledge of the negotiations.  German Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s government is
“skeptical” of such a move, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Randow in Frankfurt at 
